bon=Air Force Overseas Short Tour Service Ribbon.svg|width=80}}\n|[[Overseas Service Ribbon#Air Force|Air Force Overseas Short Tour Service Ribbon]]\n|-\n|{{ribbon devices|number=0|type=oak|ribbon=Air Force Overseas Long Tour Service Ribbon.svg|width=80}}\n|[[Overseas Service Ribbon#Air Force|Air Force Overseas Long Tour Service Ribbon]]\n|-\n|{{ribbon devices|number=8|type=oak|ribbon=Air Force Longevity Service ribbon.svg|width=80}}\n|[[Air Force Longevity Service Award]] with one silver and three bronze oak leaf clusters\n|-\n|{{ribbon devices|number=0|type=service-star|ribbon=USAF Marksmanship ribbon.svg|width=80}}\n|[[Marksmanship Ribbon|Small Arms Expert Marksmanship Ribbon]]\n|-\n|{{ribbon devices|number=0|type=service-star|ribbon=Air Force Training Ribbon.svg|width=80}}\n|[[Air Force Training Ribbon]]\n|-\n|[[File:The Khalifiyyeh Order of Bahrain, 1st class.png|80px]]\n|Khalifiyyeh Order of Bahrain, Grand Cross\n|-\n|[[File:King Faisal Award, 2d Class Ribbon.png|80px]]\n|King Faisal Order, Officer\n|-\n|[[File:Grand Cross Military Merit Order UAE.png|80px]]\n|United Arab Emirates Military Merit Order, Grand Cross\n|-\n|[[File:Legion Honneur Officier ribbon.svg|80px]]\n|[[Legion of Honour]], Officer (France)\n|-\n|[[File:MSC ribbon-military.png|80px]]\n|[[Meritorious Service Cross]], Military Division (Canada)\n|-\n|{{ribbon devices|number=1|type=service-star|ribbon=Nicaraguan Medal of Military Merit.png|width=80}}\n|Medal of Merit (Nicaragua) with bronze star\n|-\n|[[File:Vietnam Campaign Medal ribbon with 60- clasp.svg|80px]]\n|[[Vietnam Campaign Medal]]\n|-\n|[[File:Kuwait Liberation Medal (Saudi Arabia) ribbon.svg|80px]]\n|[[Kuwait Liberation Medal (Saudi Arabia)]]\n|-\n|[[File:Kuwait Liberation Medal (Kuwait) ribbon.svg|80px]]\n|[[Kuwait Liberation Medal (Kuwait)]]\n|}\n\n==Other achievements==\n*1991 U.S. News Trophy\n*1991 History of Aviation Award\n*1991 Maxwell A. Kriendler Memorial Award\n*1991 Aviation Achievement Award\n*1991 Air Force Order of the Sword\n*1991 Aviation Week and Space Technology's Aerospace Laureate\n*1992 National Veteran's Award\n\n==Promotion dates==\n*[[Second Lieutenant#United States|Second Lieutenant]] June 13, 1958\n*[[First Lieutenant#United States|First Lieutenant]] June 12, 1960\n*[[Captain (United States)|Captain]] October 1, 1963\n*[[Major (United States)|Major]] June 1, 1969\n*[[Lieutenant colonel (United States)|Lieutenant Colonel]] November 1, 1973\n*[[Colonel]] February 1, 1975\n*[[Brigadier general (United States)|Brigadier General]] August 1, 1982\n*[[Major general (United States)|Major General]] July 1, 1985\n*[[Lieutenant general (United States)|Lieutenant General]] May 1, 1987\n*[[General (United States)|General]] July 1, 1992\n\n==Notes==\n{{Portal|Biography}}\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==References==\n*{{Citation|title=Every Man a Tiger: The Gulf War Air Campaign|last1=Clancy|first1=Tom|last2=Horner|first2=Chuck|publisher=Putnam|year=1999|isbn=978-0-399-14493-6|url=https://books.google.com/?id=-LRtAAAAMAAJ}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Horner, Chuck}}\n[[Category:1936 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Davenport, Iowa]]\n[[Category:United States Air Force generals]]\n[[Category:American air force personnel of the Vietnam War]]\n[[Category:American air force personnel of the Gulf War]]\n[[Category:Military leaders of the Gulf War]]\n[[Category:College of William & Mary alumni]]\n[[Category:University of Iowa alumni]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the Distinguished Flying Cross (United States)]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the Legion of Merit]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the Silver Star]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the Air Force Distinguished Service Medal]]\n[[Category:People from Okaloosa County, Florida]]\n[[Category:People from Fort Walton Beach, Florida]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the Air Medal]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the Order of the Sword (United States)]]\n", "name_user": "Rodw", "label": "safe", "comment": "Disambiguating links toRed flag