{"title_page": "Mercado de Campo de Ourique", "text_new": "{{Multiple issues|\n{{Notability|Places|date=September 2019}}\n{{More citations needed|date=September 2019}}\n}}\n[[File:Mercado de Campo de Ourique Fachada norte.jpg|thumb|left|Exterior of Mercado de Campo de Ourique]]\n[[File:Campo de Ourique Market.jpg|thumb|Interior of Mercado de Campo de Ourique]]\n\n'''Mercado de Campo de Ourique''' is a neighborhood [[food market]] located in [[Lisbon]], [[Portugal]].<ref name=\"lisbonlux\">{{Cite web| url=http://www.lisbonlux.com/lisbon-shops/mercado-de-campo-de-ourique.html | title=Mercado de Campo de Ourique, Lisboa | website=www.lisbonlux.com | language=en | access-date=2017-01-26}}</ref><ref name=\"portugalconfidential\">{{cite web| url=https://portugalconfidential.com/mercado-de-campo-de-ourique-hip-urban-market-food-lisbon/ | title=Mercado de Campo de Ourique \u2013 Hip, Urban Market for Food and Fun in Lisbon | work=Portugal Confidential | accessdate=29 April 2019 }}</ref>\n\nThe market originally opened in 1934.<ref name=\"lisbonlux\" /> It was remodelled in 1991 and most recently in 2013 by Ant\u00f3nio Maria Braga e Alberto Castro Nunes, winners of the 2019 [[Rafael Manzano Prize]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://observador.pt/especiais/gastronomicos-e-culturais-serao-assim-os-mercados-futuro/|title=Gastron\u00f3micos e culturais. Ser\u00e3o assim os mercados do futuro?|last=Coelho|first=Sara Otto|website=Observador|language=pt-PT|access-date=2020-04-21}}</ref>. The market includes gourmet food stalls.<ref name=\"portugalconfidential\" />\n\n==See also==\n* [[Mercado de San Miguel]], [[Madrid]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n{{commons category|Mercado de Campo de Ourique}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://mercadodecampodeourique.pt/?lang=en Mercado de Campo de Ourique website] {{in lang|en}}\n\n{{Lisbon landmarks}}\n{{coord missing|Portugal}}\n\n[[Category:1934 establishments in Portugal]]\n[[Category:Buildings and structures in Lisbon]]\n[[Category:Tourist attractions in Lisbon]]\n[[Category:Retail markets in Portugal]]\n[[Category:Food markets]]\n\n{{Portugal-struct-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Multiple issues|\n{{Notability|Places|date=September 2019}}\n{{More citations needed|date=September 2019}}\n}}\n[[File:Mercado de Campo de Ourique Fachada norte.jpg|thumb|Exterior of Mercado de Campo de Ourique]]\n[[File:Campo de Ourique Market.jpg|thumb|Interior of Mercado de Campo de Ourique]]\n\n'''Mercado de Campo de Ourique''' is a neighborhood [[food market]] located in [[Lisbon]], [[Portugal]].<ref name=\"lisbonlux\">{{Cite web| url=http://www.lisbonlux.com/lisbon-shops/mercado-de-campo-de-ourique.html | title=Mercado de Campo de Ourique, Lisboa | website=www.lisbonlux.com | language=en | access-date=2017-01-26}}</ref><ref name=\"portugalconfidential\">{{cite web| url=https://portugalconfidential.com/mercado-de-campo-de-ourique-hip-urban-market-food-lisbon/ | title=Mercado de Campo de Ourique \u2013 Hip, Urban Market for Food and Fun in Lisbon | work=Portugal Confidential | accessdate=29 April 2019 }}</ref>\n\nThe market originally opened in 1934.<ref name=\"lisbonlux\" /> It was remodelled in 1991 and most recently in 2013 by Ant\u00f3nio Maria Braga e Alberto Castro Nunes, winners of the 2019 [[Rafael Manzano Prize]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://observador.pt/especiais/gastronomicos-e-culturais-serao-assim-os-mercados-futuro/|title=Gastron\u00f3micos e culturais. Ser\u00e3o assim os mercados do futuro?|last=Coelho|first=Sara Otto|website=Observador|language=pt-PT|access-date=2020-04-21}}</ref>. The market includes gourmet food stalls.<ref name=\"portugalconfidential\" />\n\n==See also==\n* [[Mercado de San Miguel]], [[Madrid]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n{{commons category|Mercado de Campo de Ourique}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://mercadodecampodeourique.pt/?lang=en Mercado de Campo de Ourique website] {{in lang|en}}\n\n{{Lisbon landmarks}}\n{{coord missing|Portugal}}\n\n[[Category:1934 establishments in Portugal]]\